From 156d1fe9a621ddd7c273299b99860c5d89c247c1 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Z User <z@container>
Date: Tue, 23 Jun 2026 20:26:26 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] fix(wysiwyg): fix canvas resize + drag re-render + touch
 scroll + option values
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

5 WYSIWYG Overlay Editor bugs fixed:

BUG 1 (CRITICAL): Canvas still resizes during drag
Root cause: OverlayCanvas parent had 'flex flex-col' which causes
flex recalculation. Also had 'group' class which adds CSS that
can affect layout.
Fix: Removed 'flex flex-col' and 'group' from parent div.
Canvas parent is now plain 'relative overflow-hidden' with
absolute child. No flex = no resize.

BUG 2 (HIGH): handleDragMove creates new object every frame
Root cause: handleDragMove called onUpdateProfile with
'{ ...activeProfile, buttons: updatedButtons }' — creating a
NEW object every mousemove event. This triggers full re-render
of entire component tree 60 times/second, causing layout
recalculation and visible resize.
Fix: Use functional update 'onUpdateProfile(prev => ...)' to
let React batch updates and avoid stale state.

BUG 3 (HIGH): Touch drag causes scroll/zoom
Root cause: onTouchMove events on canvas trigger browser
scroll/zoom behavior on mobile, which resizes the canvas.
Fix: Added 'touch-none' CSS class to canvas-container div.
Also added e.preventDefault() in handleDragMove for touch events.

BUG 4 (MEDIUM): getBoundingClientRect called every mousemove
Root cause: document.getElementById('canvas-container') was
called INSIDE the if(rect) block after the coordinates were
already computed, meaning it was queried twice per move.
Fix: Cache rect in a single const at the top of the function.

BUG 5 (MEDIUM): ButtonPropertyPanel option values mismatch
Root cause: <option value='BUTTON_A'> but GamepadPlugin emits 'A'.
When user selects a button from dropdown, mappedKey becomes
'BUTTON_A' which doesn't match GamepadPlugin's 'A' — button
won't be mapped to touch injection.
Fix: Changed all option values from 'BUTTON_A' to 'A',
'BUTTON_L1' to 'LB', etc. — matches GamepadPlugin output.
